is not here anymore.

00:50:33.540 --> 00:50:35.250 align:middle line:84%
And they would move
in the direction

00:50:35.250 --> 00:50:39.420 align:middle line:84%
of the great spiritual
philosophies of the East.

00:50:39.420 --> 00:50:42.970 align:middle line:84%
Many of them would even
embrace the cosmologies

00:50:42.970 --> 00:50:45.940 align:middle line:90%
of some of the native cultures.

00:50:45.940 --> 00:50:50.160 align:middle line:84%
I have seen people who have the
best anthropological training

00:50:50.160 --> 00:50:52.570 align:middle line:84%
at Harvard and
Stanford, and after they

00:50:52.570 --> 00:50:54.680 align:middle line:84%
had these experiences,
they would end up

00:50:54.680 --> 00:50:59.072 align:middle line:84%
as apprentices of a shaman
of an illiterate culture,

00:50:59.072 --> 00:51:01.280 align:middle line:84%
because they realize they
can learn there's something

00:51:01.280 --> 00:51:04.120 align:middle line:84%
that their training,
the Western training,

00:51:04.120 --> 00:51:08.242 align:middle line:90%
couldn't possibly provide.

00:51:08.242 --> 00:51:09.950 align:middle line:84%
Many of you probably
know Michael Harner.

00:51:09.950 --> 00:51:15.370 align:middle line:84%
He's an anthropologist
in sort of good standing,

00:51:15.370 --> 00:51:18.760 align:middle line:84%
academic standing,
taught here in the New

00:51:18.760 --> 00:51:20.810 align:middle line:90%
School for Social Research.

00:51:20.810 --> 00:51:23.960 align:middle line:84%
He's now in California where
at least all these people

00:51:23.960 --> 00:51:25.220 align:middle line:90%
seem to be flocking now.

00:51:25.220 --> 00:51:28.410 align:middle line:90%


00:51:28.410 --> 00:51:32.060 align:middle line:84%
He is a trained anthropologist
who also experienced

00:51:32.060 --> 00:51:35.410 align:middle line:84%
shamanic initiation
when he was doing

00:51:35.410 --> 00:51:38.230 align:middle line:90%
field research in the Amazon.

00:51:38.230 --> 00:51:42.110 align:middle line:84%
And he wrote a book called
"The Way of the Shaman."

00:51:42.110 --> 00:51:43.857 align:middle line:84%
And in the preface
of this book, he

00:51:43.857 --> 00:51:45.190 align:middle line:90%
says something very interesting.

00:51:45.190 --> 00:51:47.370 align:middle line:84%
He says that from
his dual prospective,

00:51:47.370 --> 00:51:51.160 align:middle line:84%
as a Western trained
academician, and also somebody

00:51:51.160 --> 00:51:54.700 align:middle line:84%
who experienced personally
shamanic initiation,

00:51:54.700 --> 00:51:58.250 align:middle line:84%
that Western psychology and
psychiatry is seriously biased

00:51:58.250 --> 00:52:00.750 align:middle line:90%
in at least two important ways.

00:52:00.750 --> 00:52:05.510 align:middle line:84%
It is ethnocentric and
it is cognicentric.

00:52:05.510 --> 00:52:07.180 align:middle line:90%
And I will explain it.

00:52:07.180 --> 00:52:09.046 align:middle line:84%
Now, everybody
understand ethnocentric?

00:52:09.046 --> 00:52:14.600 align:middle line:84%
It means Western
psychiatry and psychology

00:52:14.600 --> 00:52:19.790 align:middle line:84%
has a certain perspective on
the psyche in health and disease

00:52:19.790 --> 00:52:22.540 align:middle line:84%
that was developed by a
small group of people,

00:52:22.540 --> 00:52:25.700 align:middle line:84%
by, again, the monastic
materialistic group

00:52:25.700 --> 00:52:29.480 align:middle line:84%
of scientists in the
industrial civilization.

00:52:29.480 --> 00:52:32.120 align:middle line:84%
Now this group considers
its own perspective

00:52:32.120 --> 00:52:35.910 align:middle line:84%
to be absolutely superior
to any perspective

00:52:35.910 --> 00:52:39.390 align:middle line:90%
that anybody had ever anywhere.

00:52:39.390 --> 00:52:41.660 align:middle line:84%
So anything that in
ritual spiritual life

00:52:41.660 --> 00:52:45.220 align:middle line:84%
of other cultures doesn't make
sense to a Freudian analyst

00:52:45.220 --> 00:52:49.830 align:middle line:84%
or to behaviors would be
called primitive, magical,

00:52:49.830 --> 00:52:53.550 align:middle line:84%
superstitial, borderline
kind of stuff.

00:52:53.550 --> 00:52:57.300 align:middle line:90%


00:52:57.300 --> 00:53:01.440 align:middle line:84%
If you would take a Western
trained psychiatrist who

00:53:01.440 --> 00:53:05.920 align:middle line:84%
buys that trip, or an
anthropologist to India,

00:53:05.920 --> 00:53:09.060 align:middle line:84%
and show them what the yogis
and the sadhus are doing there,

00:53:09.060 --> 00:53:11.970 align:middle line:90%
they would get a diagnosis.

00:53:11.970 --> 00:53:17.390 align:middle line:84%
At least ambulatory,
psychotic, if not more.

00:53:17.390 --> 00:53:22.210 align:middle line:84%
The same with shamans,
I already mentioned it.

00:53:22.210 --> 00:53:24.030 align:middle line:84%
But because it's
ethnocentric, it also

00:53:24.030 --> 00:53:25.980 align:middle line:90%
works the other way around.

00:53:25.980 --> 00:53:30.040 align:middle line:84%
If you would take a shaman
from central Mexico, which

00:53:30.040 --> 00:53:32.690 align:middle line:84%
we have done, and
take that person who

00:53:32.690 --> 00:53:35.030 align:middle line:84%
comes from a culture
that has any sense

00:53:35.030 --> 00:53:39.530 align:middle line:84%
of our biological nature, any
sense for cycles in nature,

00:53:39.530 --> 00:53:41.870 align:middle line:84%
cycles in the cosmos,
would take them

00:53:41.870 --> 00:53:45.405 align:middle line:84%
to a place like Los
Angeles, and I'm not just

00:53:45.405 --> 00:53:48.030 align:middle line:84%
talking about the time when they
were burning their own houses,

00:53:48.030 --> 00:53:53.010 align:middle line:84%
but just an ordinary day
in Los Angeles, a person

00:53:53.010 --> 00:53:55.760 align:middle line:84%
from that kind of culture would
think that we have completely

00:53:55.760 --> 00:53:56.390 align:middle line:90%
lost it.

00:53:56.390 --> 00:53:58.620 align:middle line:84%
We don't know where
the priorities are.

00:53:58.620 --> 00:54:00.130 align:middle line:90%
We are biological creatures.

00:54:00.130 --> 00:54:01.880 align:middle line:90%
We depend on the earth.

00:54:01.880 --> 00:54:02.895 align:middle line:90%
We depend on water.

00:54:02.895 --> 00:54:05.430 align:middle line:90%
We depend critically on air.

00:54:05.430 --> 00:54:07.540 align:middle line:90%
We have contaminated it all.

00:54:07.540 --> 00:54:10.930 align:middle line:84%
We have spoiled
the earth, spoiled

00:54:10.930 --> 00:54:16.690 align:middle line:90%
the water, spoiled the air.

00:54:16.690 --> 00:54:18.680 align:middle line:84%
In Los Angeles and
other places, we've

00:54:18.680 --> 00:54:24.840 align:middle line:84%
covered every square yard with
asphalt, with cement, and so

00:54:24.840 --> 00:54:29.780 align:middle line:84%
on, going to more
money, power, status,

00:54:29.780 --> 00:54:33.500 align:middle line:84%
tripling, quadrupling the gross
national product, absolutely

00:54:33.500 --> 00:54:40.690 align:middle line:84%
linear kind of an
orientation, kind

00:54:40.690 --> 00:54:46.230 align:middle line:84%
of squandering
nonrenewable resources

00:54:46.230 --> 00:54:50.622 align:middle line:90%
and turning them into pollution.

00:54:50.622 --> 00:54:52.580 align:middle line:84%
So somebody who comes
from that kind of culture

00:54:52.580 --> 00:54:54.620 align:middle line:84%
will thing that we have
completely lost it.

00:54:54.620 --> 00:54:55.900 align:middle line:90%
We are crazy.

00:54:55.900 --> 00:54:58.530 align:middle line:90%
We are insane.

00:54:58.530 --> 00:55:03.280 align:middle line:84%
Now the second thing
that Michael says,

00:55:03.280 --> 00:55:10.380 align:middle line:84%
psychiatry and psychology
is also cognicentric.

00:55:10.380 --> 00:55:13.310 align:middle line:84%
Now cognicentric,
probably a better term

00:55:13.310 --> 00:55:18.810 align:middle line:84%
would be pragnocentric, means
that we have built our theories

00:55:18.810 --> 00:55:22.550 align:middle line:84%
in psychology and psychiatry
exclusively on evidence

00:55:22.550 --> 00:55:26.270 align:middle line:84%
that comes from observations
done in the hilotropic state,

00:55:26.270 --> 00:55:28.920 align:middle line:84%
in the ordinary state
of consciousness.

00:55:28.920 --> 00:55:32.860 align:middle line:84%
Now the exception is
dreams, if the dreams don't

00:55:32.860 --> 00:55:35.150 align:middle line:84%
repeat themselves
and if they are not

00:55:35.150 --> 00:55:36.970 align:middle line:90%
associated with anxiety.

00:55:36.970 --> 00:55:38.580 align:middle line:84%
And even dreams
are pathological.

00:55:38.580 --> 00:55:41.740 align:middle line:84%
But you can have just
the ordinary variety

00:55:41.740 --> 00:55:43.830 align:middle line:90%
and get away with it.

00:55:43.830 --> 00:55:47.310 align:middle line:84%
So if you think about it,
we have an enormous amount

00:55:47.310 --> 00:55:51.640 align:middle line:84%
of evidence that we have
amassed in different avenues

00:55:51.640 --> 00:55:53.270 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness research.

00:55:53.270 --> 00:55:56.080 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not just talk about
the psychedelic research, which

00:55:56.080 --> 00:56:00.490 align:middle line:84%
certainly has produced an
enormous amount of evidence

00:56:00.490 --> 00:56:03.290 align:middle line:84%
published in scientific
articles and books.

00:56:03.290 --> 00:56:09.910 align:middle line:84%
But look at the studies in
parapsychology, well documented

00:56:09.910 --> 00:56:13.280 align:middle line:84%
methodologically sound,
statistically sound,

00:56:13.280 --> 00:56:16.970 align:middle line:90%
that have been discarded.

00:56:16.970 --> 00:56:19.860 align:middle line:84%
What's happening today in
powerful experiential forms

00:56:19.860 --> 00:56:21.080 align:middle line:90%
of psychotherapy?

00:56:21.080 --> 00:56:23.890 align:middle line:84%
People experiencing,
reliving their birth,

00:56:23.890 --> 00:56:27.300 align:middle line:84%
experiencing prenatal
experiences, having past life

00:56:27.300 --> 00:56:28.090 align:middle line:90%
experiences.

00:56:28.090 --> 00:56:34.350 align:middle line:84%
None of that has been taken into
consideration by our psychiatry

00:56:34.350 --> 00:56:34.980 align:middle line:90%
and psychology.

00:56:34.980 --> 00:56:40.140 align:middle line:84%
We still use a model which is
limited to postnatal biography

00:56:40.140 --> 00:56:42.630 align:middle line:90%
and the individual unconscious.

00:56:42.630 --> 00:56:45.890 align:middle line:90%


00:56:45.890 --> 00:56:50.550 align:middle line:84%
Something that's astonishing
is how the evidence

00:56:50.550 --> 00:56:52.030 align:middle line:90%
from thanatology is ignored.

00:56:52.030 --> 00:56:56.260 align:middle line:84%
I mentioned last night the
work of thanatologists, showing

00:56:56.260 --> 00:56:59.320 align:middle line:84%
that disembodied
consciousness maintains,

00:56:59.320 --> 00:57:02.170 align:middle line:84%
in a near death situation,
maintains the capacity

00:57:02.170 --> 00:57:07.860 align:middle line:84%
to perceive the environment,
the immediate environment--

00:57:07.860 --> 00:57:10.130 align:middle line:84%
rooms behind the walls
or something that's

00:57:10.130 --> 00:57:13.500 align:middle line:90%
happening in remote locations.

00:57:13.500 --> 00:57:17.430 align:middle line:84%
Blind people are capable of
seeing when their consciousness

00:57:17.430 --> 00:57:18.330 align:middle line:90%
leaves the body.

00:57:18.330 --> 00:57:22.120 align:middle line:84%
And those are major,
major paradigm

00:57:22.120 --> 00:57:23.940 align:middle line:90%
challenging observations.

00:57:23.940 --> 00:57:26.500 align:middle line:84%
And if you think how little
the physicists needed

00:57:26.500 --> 00:57:29.620 align:middle line:84%
in the first three
decades of the century

00:57:29.620 --> 00:57:34.070 align:middle line:84%
to change somehow radically
the image of physics,

00:57:34.070 --> 00:57:36.510 align:middle line:84%
we have an enormous
amount of evidence

00:57:36.510 --> 00:57:38.290 align:middle line:90%
from all these different areas.

00:57:38.290 --> 00:57:43.780 align:middle line:84%
And it has been ignored,
as far as these near death

00:57:43.780 --> 00:57:45.450 align:middle line:90%
experiences are concerned.

00:57:45.450 --> 00:57:47.080 align:middle line:90%
People in the street know that.

00:57:47.080 --> 00:57:50.390 align:middle line:84%
We have talk shows
where thanatologists

00:57:50.390 --> 00:57:53.350 align:middle line:84%
are talking about their
experiences, people

00:57:53.350 --> 00:57:56.820 align:middle line:84%
who had these experiences
talk about them.

00:57:56.820 --> 00:57:58.630 align:middle line:84%
Some of the books
describing them

00:57:58.630 --> 00:58:01.900 align:middle line:84%
made the New York
Best Seller List.

00:58:01.900 --> 00:58:05.760 align:middle line:84%
A number of Hollywood
movies portray these kind

00:58:05.760 --> 00:58:09.710 align:middle line:84%
of out-of-body experiences
with maintaining perception,

00:58:09.710 --> 00:58:10.930 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:58:10.930 --> 00:58:14.810 align:middle line:84%
And the academic circles have
not responded to it at all.

00:58:14.810 --> 00:58:17.830 align:middle line:90%


00:58:17.830 --> 00:58:22.170 align:middle line:84%
John Mack who talked yesterday
was working with a group,

00:58:22.170 --> 00:58:24.190 align:middle line:90%
studying anomalous experiences.

00:58:24.190 --> 00:58:27.740 align:middle line:84%
This is just one of
many, these thanatologic.

00:58:27.740 --> 00:58:31.280 align:middle line:84%
We really have a major,
major challenging evidence

00:58:31.280 --> 00:58:32.790 align:middle line:90%
that has been ignored.

00:58:32.790 --> 00:58:37.820 align:middle line:84%
And this is with Michael
calls cognicentric bias.

00:58:37.820 --> 00:58:41.900 align:middle line:84%
We have simply a censored
out, vast amount of evidence

00:58:41.900 --> 00:58:46.070 align:middle line:84%
coming from these
holotropic states.

00:58:46.070 --> 00:58:48.860 align:middle line:84%
So the question
now would be, what

00:58:48.860 --> 00:58:54.030 align:middle line:84%
would be psychology
and psychiatry,

00:58:54.030 --> 00:58:59.470 align:middle line:84%
if it were not ethnocentric, if
it were culturally sensitive,

00:58:59.470 --> 00:59:02.430 align:middle line:84%
if it treated with
respect the ritual

00:59:02.430 --> 00:59:07.020 align:middle line:84%
and spiritual life
of other cultures?

00:59:07.020 --> 00:59:09.430 align:middle line:84%
And what psychiatry
and psychology

00:59:09.430 --> 00:59:13.190 align:middle line:84%
would look like if it
were not cognicentric,

00:59:13.190 --> 00:59:17.190 align:middle line:84%
if it would really open itself
to the overwhelming evidence

00:59:17.190 --> 00:59:21.250 align:middle line:84%
that's coming from modern
consciousness research?

00:59:21.250 --> 00:59:23.210 align:middle line:84%
So I can think
about at least five

00:59:23.210 --> 00:59:27.090 align:middle line:84%
or six areas in which we
would absolutely radically

00:59:27.090 --> 00:59:29.840 align:middle line:90%
have to change our thinking.

00:59:29.840 --> 00:59:33.630 align:middle line:84%
Now you will understand
why this is not happening,

00:59:33.630 --> 00:59:37.910 align:middle line:84%
why the academic circles are
showing such resistance to this

00:59:37.910 --> 00:59:40.690 align:middle line:84%
evidence, because it cannot
be handled by a little what we

00:59:40.690 --> 00:59:44.300 align:middle line:84%
call ad hoc hypothesis, a
little patchwork here and there.

00:59:44.300 --> 00:59:46.140 align:middle line:90%
This is a major overhaul.

00:59:46.140 --> 00:59:49.200 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we would have to do
that what we have been teaching

00:59:49.200 --> 00:59:53.150 align:middle line:90%
is nonsense, is not true.

00:59:53.150 --> 00:59:55.160 align:middle line:84%
So the first of
these areas would

00:59:55.160 --> 00:59:57.960 align:middle line:84%
relate to something
very fundamental, which

00:59:57.960 --> 00:59:59.870 align:middle line:90%
is the nature of consciousness.

00:59:59.870 --> 01:00:04.020 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness is seen
by the academic circles

01:00:04.020 --> 01:00:07.370 align:middle line:84%
as somehow mysteriously
emerging out

01:00:07.370 --> 01:00:10.510 align:middle line:84%
of the complexity of the
neurophysiological processes

01:00:10.510 --> 01:00:11.570 align:middle line:90%
in the brain.

01:00:11.570 --> 01:00:13.510 align:middle line:84%
Now if you think
about it, the gap

01:00:13.510 --> 01:00:16.880 align:middle line:84%
between matter and
consciousness is so radical

01:00:16.880 --> 01:00:20.710 align:middle line:84%
that it's very,
very hard to imagine

01:00:20.710 --> 01:00:25.870 align:middle line:84%
how that could be bridged, how
something that's dead, inert,

01:00:25.870 --> 01:00:32.430 align:middle line:84%
reactive would suddenly
become aware of itself

01:00:32.430 --> 01:00:39.110 align:middle line:84%
and be capable of developing
life and intelligence.

01:00:39.110 --> 01:00:42.730 align:middle line:84%
And these are
metaphysical assumptions

01:00:42.730 --> 01:00:48.980 align:middle line:84%
that are camouflaged
as scientific theories.

01:00:48.980 --> 01:00:51.710 align:middle line:84%
There's absolutely
no evidence that I

01:00:51.710 --> 01:00:54.550 align:middle line:84%
know about showing
that consciousness

01:00:54.550 --> 01:00:56.724 align:middle line:90%
is generated in the brain.

01:00:56.724 --> 01:01:00.540 align:middle line:84%
We have enormous
evidence showing

01:01:00.540 --> 01:01:03.860 align:middle line:84%
that there's a
correlation between things

01:01:03.860 --> 01:01:07.550 align:middle line:84%
that are happening in the brain
and states of consciousness.

01:01:07.550 --> 01:01:09.370 align:middle line:84%
If we have a temporal
tumor, you can

01:01:09.370 --> 01:01:11.540 align:middle line:84%
have certain kinds of
changes in consciousness,

01:01:11.540 --> 01:01:14.720 align:middle line:84%
different from when you
have a prefrontal tumor

01:01:14.720 --> 01:01:17.830 align:middle line:90%
or a suboccipital tumor.

01:01:17.830 --> 01:01:22.670 align:middle line:84%
Somebody hits you over the head
or compresses your carotids,

01:01:22.670 --> 01:01:24.520 align:middle line:90%
you lose consciousness.

01:01:24.520 --> 01:01:29.710 align:middle line:84%
You take LSD, your consciousness
changes, and so on.

01:01:29.710 --> 01:01:32.030 align:middle line:84%
Nobody is arguing this
is kind of evidence.

01:01:32.030 --> 01:01:35.440 align:middle line:90%
This is blatantly true.

01:01:35.440 --> 01:01:38.335 align:middle line:84%
But then there's a
logical jump which

01:01:38.335 --> 01:01:40.900 align:middle line:84%
is that because there is
this kind of connection,

01:01:40.900 --> 01:01:42.845 align:middle line:84%
it means that
consciousness actually

01:01:42.845 --> 01:01:44.650 align:middle line:90%
is concocted in the brain.

01:01:44.650 --> 01:01:47.110 align:middle line:90%
And that's a whole other story.

01:01:47.110 --> 01:01:52.810 align:middle line:84%
We have the same connection
in the television set.

01:01:52.810 --> 01:01:55.970 align:middle line:84%
The quality of the
picture and of the sound

01:01:55.970 --> 01:02:00.820 align:middle line:84%
depends critically on
the component of the set.

01:02:00.820 --> 01:02:02.130 align:middle line:90%
Now what does it mean?

01:02:02.130 --> 01:02:04.530 align:middle line:84%
It means that there is
a critical connection

01:02:04.530 --> 01:02:06.730 align:middle line:84%
between the quality
of the program

01:02:06.730 --> 01:02:09.240 align:middle line:90%
and the functioning of the set.

01:02:09.240 --> 01:02:12.600 align:middle line:84%
Where the program is coming
from is a whole other question.

01:02:12.600 --> 01:02:15.210 align:middle line:84%
We would laugh at
somebody who would go down

01:02:15.210 --> 01:02:18.340 align:middle line:84%
to molecular level and
the different condensers

01:02:18.340 --> 01:02:22.840 align:middle line:84%
and the wires and believe that
if he or she can understand

01:02:22.840 --> 01:02:24.460 align:middle line:84%
everything about
the box, they're

01:02:24.460 --> 01:02:26.670 align:middle line:84%
going to understand
why at 7 o'clock

01:02:26.670 --> 01:02:30.540 align:middle line:84%
Ed Sullivan showed up with
the Beatles on the thing.

01:02:30.540 --> 01:02:33.190 align:middle line:84%
So obviously there
is an alternative way

01:02:33.190 --> 01:02:35.130 align:middle line:90%
off interpreting this data.

01:02:35.130 --> 01:02:36.590 align:middle line:90%
There is a connection.

01:02:36.590 --> 01:02:42.170 align:middle line:84%
But what it is showing may be
that the brain is necessary,

01:02:42.170 --> 01:02:44.460 align:middle line:84%
that it mediates on
our consciousness,

01:02:44.460 --> 01:02:46.890 align:middle line:84%
but there is no
reason to see this

01:02:46.890 --> 01:02:51.210 align:middle line:84%
has an absolute scientific proof
that consciousness actually

01:02:51.210 --> 01:02:53.120 align:middle line:90%
comes from the brain.

01:02:53.120 --> 01:02:54.960 align:middle line:84%
So this is the first
major radical change

01:02:54.960 --> 01:02:57.160 align:middle line:90%
we would have to make.

01:02:57.160 --> 01:03:02.180 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness very likely is
not generated by the brain.

01:03:02.180 --> 01:03:05.980 align:middle line:84%
It's a universal phenomenon
in which we all participate

01:03:05.980 --> 01:03:08.710 align:middle line:90%
through our individual psyche.

01:03:08.710 --> 01:03:11.470 align:middle line:84%
And as I mentioned, we can
dissolve those boundaries

01:03:11.470 --> 01:03:15.230 align:middle line:84%
and we can experience larger
and larger parts of this field

01:03:15.230 --> 01:03:17.840 align:middle line:90%
of universal consciousness.

01:03:17.840 --> 01:03:20.770 align:middle line:84%
Now the second major change
we would have to make

01:03:20.770 --> 01:03:24.980 align:middle line:84%
is in what I would call the
cartography of the psyche.

01:03:24.980 --> 01:03:28.500 align:middle line:84%
We have a model which is
limited to postnatal biography

01:03:28.500 --> 01:03:31.425 align:middle line:84%
and to the individual
unconscious.

01:03:31.425 --> 01:03:34.120 align:middle line:90%


01:03:34.120 --> 01:03:38.390 align:middle line:84%
Freud said that a
newborn is a tabula rasa,

01:03:38.390 --> 01:03:41.850 align:middle line:84%
is a clean slate,
so there's nothing

01:03:41.850 --> 01:03:45.820 align:middle line:84%
of interest for psychologists
that precedes birth, including

01:03:45.820 --> 01:03:47.040 align:middle line:90%
birth itself.

01:03:47.040 --> 01:03:51.370 align:middle line:84%
Now this is a fantastic
thing in current psychiatry.

01:03:51.370 --> 01:03:55.410 align:middle line:84%
We ask people about birth,
but the reason for it

01:03:55.410 --> 01:03:58.120 align:middle line:84%
is that if it was
really bad, it could

01:03:58.120 --> 01:04:00.350 align:middle line:90%
have damaged your brain cells.

01:04:00.350 --> 01:04:03.071 align:middle line:84%
As long as it didn't
irreversibly damage your brain

01:04:03.071 --> 01:04:04.320 align:middle line:90%
cells, it is not psychotrauma.

01:04:04.320 --> 01:04:07.250 align:middle line:90%


01:04:07.250 --> 01:04:11.990 align:middle line:84%
So we have this concept that
the experience of birth, which

01:04:11.990 --> 01:04:16.660 align:middle line:84%
could be 20, 30, 40, 50 hours
of a life-threatening situation,

01:04:16.660 --> 01:04:20.730 align:middle line:90%
is not a psychotrauma.

01:04:20.730 --> 01:04:25.620 align:middle line:84%
Now on the other hand, there
is a very clearly general

01:04:25.620 --> 01:04:29.510 align:middle line:84%
agreement that immediately
afterwards, nuances of nursing

01:04:29.510 --> 01:04:33.750 align:middle line:84%
are all important, even
gynecologists or obstetricians

01:04:33.750 --> 01:04:37.170 align:middle line:84%
talk about bonding,
or pediatricians talk

01:04:37.170 --> 01:04:42.130 align:middle line:84%
about bonding, the importance
of the visual contact

01:04:42.130 --> 01:04:44.060 align:middle line:84%
between the mother
and the child.

01:04:44.060 --> 01:04:47.520 align:middle line:84%
The general agreement that
experiences in nursing

01:04:47.520 --> 01:04:49.390 align:middle line:90%
can really shape personality.

01:04:49.390 --> 01:04:51.990 align:middle line:90%


01:04:51.990 --> 01:04:57.130 align:middle line:84%
Sullivan talks about the little
child, a little infant nursing,

01:04:57.130 --> 01:05:00.966 align:middle line:84%
distinguishing a good nipple,
evil nipple, and wrong nipple.

01:05:00.966 --> 01:05:03.040 align:middle line:84%
The good nipple is a
nipple that gives you milk,

01:05:03.040 --> 01:05:05.200 align:middle line:84%
and the mother is a loving
mother that holds you

01:05:05.200 --> 01:05:06.480 align:middle line:90%
the right way and so on.

01:05:06.480 --> 01:05:09.320 align:middle line:84%
The evil nipple is nipple
that gives you milk,

01:05:09.320 --> 01:05:12.660 align:middle line:84%
but the mother is
rejecting or unloving.

01:05:12.660 --> 01:05:14.770 align:middle line:90%
The milk is kind of sour.

01:05:14.770 --> 01:05:17.672 align:middle line:84%
And then the wrong nipple
is like your thumb.

01:05:17.672 --> 01:05:20.860 align:middle line:84%
You just suck it and it
doesn't even give you milk.

01:05:20.860 --> 01:05:26.427 align:middle line:84%
So the infant responds
to nuances of nursing.

01:05:26.427 --> 01:05:28.010 align:middle line:84%
Now with this kind
of thinking that we

01:05:28.010 --> 01:05:29.590 align:middle line:84%
have in current
psychiatry, you're

01:05:29.590 --> 01:05:33.080 align:middle line:84%
asked to believe that it's
possible to go through hours

01:05:33.080 --> 01:05:38.430 align:middle line:84%
of a life-threatening situation
involving pain, choking,

01:05:38.430 --> 01:05:39.790 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

01:05:39.790 --> 01:05:42.010 align:middle line:84%
The child didn't notice
that something strange

01:05:42.010 --> 01:05:42.980 align:middle line:90%
was happening.

01:05:42.980 --> 01:05:45.150 align:middle line:90%
It's not recorded anywhere.

01:05:45.150 --> 01:05:48.670 align:middle line:84%
But instantly after
coming out to the breast,

01:05:48.670 --> 01:05:51.090 align:middle line:84%
the child becomes
this-- or the infant

01:05:51.090 --> 01:05:55.380 align:middle line:84%
becomes this connoisseur
of female nipples.

01:05:55.380 --> 01:05:57.180 align:middle line:90%
Things are not quite right.

01:05:57.180 --> 01:05:59.700 align:middle line:84%
Mommy's not holding
me the right way.

01:05:59.700 --> 01:06:03.900 align:middle line:84%
So obviously those are important
things in earliest, or nursing

01:06:03.900 --> 01:06:05.440 align:middle line:90%
is phenomenally important.

01:06:05.440 --> 01:06:09.140 align:middle line:84%
But so is birth, and if you
have a holotropic state,

01:06:09.140 --> 01:06:11.390 align:middle line:84%
you'll find out that
the record is there

01:06:11.390 --> 01:06:14.850 align:middle line:84%
and that it's very,
very important.

01:06:14.850 --> 01:06:19.240 align:middle line:84%
Now the usual reason that
is given by births cannot be

01:06:19.240 --> 01:06:21.930 align:middle line:84%
important is the cortex
is not myelinized,

01:06:21.930 --> 01:06:23.550 align:middle line:90%
the cortex is not finished.

01:06:23.550 --> 01:06:26.610 align:middle line:90%


01:06:26.610 --> 01:06:32.350 align:middle line:84%
Now Eric Kandel from Sweden
just got a Nobel Prize

01:06:32.350 --> 01:06:37.380 align:middle line:84%
for showing-- he was working
with a sea slug, Aplysia,

01:06:37.380 --> 01:06:40.510 align:middle line:90%
studying memory in the sea slug.

01:06:40.510 --> 01:06:46.170 align:middle line:84%
So we are denying that a
newborn can remember something

01:06:46.170 --> 01:06:51.230 align:middle line:84%
like 30 hours of delivery,
but a sea slug has memory.

01:06:51.230 --> 01:06:55.770 align:middle line:90%


01:06:55.770 --> 01:06:58.610 align:middle line:84%
So we have to have a
much larger cartography.

01:06:58.610 --> 01:07:01.280 align:middle line:84%
Certainly there is
the biographical level

01:07:01.280 --> 01:07:04.120 align:middle line:84%
that is described
by psychoanalysis,

01:07:04.120 --> 01:07:05.810 align:middle line:84%
but then there is
the perinatal level.

01:07:05.810 --> 01:07:08.320 align:middle line:84%
There's a very important
imprint of birth,

01:07:08.320 --> 01:07:12.850 align:middle line:84%
and then there is also the
whole transpersonal level.

01:07:12.850 --> 01:07:16.960 align:middle line:84%
I described the experiences of
identifying with other people,

01:07:16.960 --> 01:07:18.840 align:middle line:84%
experiencing group
consciousness,

01:07:18.840 --> 01:07:24.470 align:middle line:84%
experiencing with experiences
of animal consciousness,

01:07:24.470 --> 01:07:26.230 align:middle line:90%
plant consciousness, and so on.

01:07:26.230 --> 01:07:28.610 align:middle line:84%
The third one would
be, if we have

01:07:28.610 --> 01:07:32.360 align:middle line:84%
emotional and psychosomatic
problems, according

01:07:32.360 --> 01:07:39.240 align:middle line:84%
to traditional psychiatry, the
whole history is postnatal.

01:07:39.240 --> 01:07:42.330 align:middle line:84%
In other words, things happen
to us in infancy, in childhood,

01:07:42.330 --> 01:07:43.570 align:middle line:90%
and later in life.

01:07:43.570 --> 01:07:46.620 align:middle line:84%
If something is not organic,
it can be fully explained

01:07:46.620 --> 01:07:48.600 align:middle line:90%
from postnatal history.

01:07:48.600 --> 01:07:50.380 align:middle line:84%
If you work with
holotropic states,

01:07:50.380 --> 01:07:53.900 align:middle line:84%
you always find something
in biographical history.

01:07:53.900 --> 01:07:57.730 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, there
are additional deeper roots

01:07:57.730 --> 01:08:01.450 align:middle line:84%
that go to the perinatal
and even deeper

01:08:01.450 --> 01:08:02.930 align:middle line:90%
roots that are transpersonal.

01:08:02.930 --> 01:08:06.750 align:middle line:84%
For example, karmic,
for example, archetypal.

01:08:06.750 --> 01:08:10.120 align:middle line:84%
So behind emotional and
psychosomatic problems,

01:08:10.120 --> 01:08:14.360 align:middle line:84%
there is a multi-level
sort of dynamic system

01:08:14.360 --> 01:08:18.399 align:middle line:84%
that has to be confronted
in an effective therapy.

01:08:18.399 --> 01:08:22.029 align:middle line:90%


01:08:22.029 --> 01:08:28.390 align:middle line:84%
I will just mention
one important area when

01:08:28.390 --> 01:08:30.450 align:middle line:84%
we get new insights,
which has to do

01:08:30.450 --> 01:08:32.979 align:middle line:84%
with the strategy
of self exploration,

01:08:32.979 --> 01:08:35.450 align:middle line:90%
or the strategy of therapy.

01:08:35.450 --> 01:08:39.700 align:middle line:84%
We have many, many different
schools of psychotherapy.

01:08:39.700 --> 01:08:41.430 align:middle line:84%
Each of those schools
says something

01:08:41.430 --> 01:08:44.060 align:middle line:84%
very different about what
are the important forces

01:08:44.060 --> 01:08:46.640 align:middle line:84%
in the psyche, why
symptoms develop,

01:08:46.640 --> 01:08:48.319 align:middle line:90%
what the symptoms mean.

01:08:48.319 --> 01:08:52.800 align:middle line:84%
And each of these schools will
give us a different technique

01:08:52.800 --> 01:08:59.010 align:middle line:84%
that we use with clients to
quote, unquote, fix them.

01:08:59.010 --> 01:09:02.650 align:middle line:84%
And there's absolute lack
of unanimity about this.

01:09:02.650 --> 01:09:04.880 align:middle line:84%
So if you have a problem,
you can flip a coin,

01:09:04.880 --> 01:09:06.970 align:middle line:84%
you choose a school,
which each school

01:09:06.970 --> 01:09:11.010 align:middle line:84%
you get a different story
about what's wrong with you,

01:09:11.010 --> 01:09:14.359 align:middle line:84%
and in each school you will
be offered a different method.

01:09:14.359 --> 01:09:16.700 align:middle line:84%
So the idea is you can
understand the psyche

01:09:16.700 --> 01:09:18.760 align:middle line:84%
with your head,
with your intellect.

01:09:18.760 --> 01:09:22.580 align:middle line:84%
You can sort of come up with
some kind of a bag of tricks

01:09:22.580 --> 01:09:26.710 align:middle line:84%
that you can sort of
straighten out the situation.

01:09:26.710 --> 01:09:29.300 align:middle line:84%
Now this work with
holotropic states

01:09:29.300 --> 01:09:32.580 align:middle line:84%
shows a radically
different approach

01:09:32.580 --> 01:09:36.069 align:middle line:84%
to this, which is in
a holotropic state,

01:09:36.069 --> 01:09:42.410 align:middle line:84%
you immobilise your own
inner healing intelligence.

01:09:42.410 --> 01:09:44.350 align:middle line:84%
This is really something
that Jung was talking

01:09:44.350 --> 01:09:47.370 align:middle line:90%
about in different words.

01:09:47.370 --> 01:09:51.189 align:middle line:84%
For Jung, it was impossible
to use your intellect

01:09:51.189 --> 01:09:53.900 align:middle line:90%
to understand the psyche.

01:09:53.900 --> 01:09:55.400 align:middle line:84%
The reason for that
is the intellect

01:09:55.400 --> 01:10:00.680 align:middle line:84%
is just a tool that helps
us to orient ourselves

01:10:00.680 --> 01:10:05.900 align:middle line:90%
in the practical situations.

01:10:05.900 --> 01:10:09.250 align:middle line:84%
The psyche in the Jungian
understanding is cosmic.

01:10:09.250 --> 01:10:10.990 align:middle line:90%
The psyche is anima mundi.

01:10:10.990 --> 01:10:14.020 align:middle line:84%
This is the consciousness
and the intelligence that

01:10:14.020 --> 01:10:15.890 align:middle line:90%
permeates all of existence.

01:10:15.890 --> 01:10:18.210 align:middle line:84%
And our individual
psyche is teased out

01:10:18.210 --> 01:10:20.570 align:middle line:90%
of this cosmic matrix.

01:10:20.570 --> 01:10:22.860 align:middle line:84%
And as I mentioned, in
transpersonal states,

01:10:22.860 --> 01:10:24.830 align:middle line:84%
we can expand our
consciousness and we

01:10:24.830 --> 01:10:30.650 align:middle line:84%
can experience larger and
larger pieces of this matrix.

01:10:30.650 --> 01:10:33.590 align:middle line:84%
So the intellect cannot
understand the psyche.

01:10:33.590 --> 01:10:36.990 align:middle line:84%
So for Jung, the alternative
was, what we can do,

01:10:36.990 --> 01:10:41.950 align:middle line:84%
we can create a sort of
a supportive environment.

01:10:41.950 --> 01:10:45.870 align:middle line:84%
And the Jungian model for
that is the hermetic vessel.

01:10:45.870 --> 01:10:48.930 align:middle line:84%
Jung was very interested in
alchemy, the hermetic vessel

01:10:48.930 --> 01:10:50.820 align:middle line:90%
where transformation happens.

01:10:50.820 --> 01:10:52.880 align:middle line:84%
So we create a
supportive framework.

01:10:52.880 --> 01:10:58.860 align:middle line:84%
We give a method to the client
through which the conscious ego

01:10:58.860 --> 01:11:02.130 align:middle line:84%
can now communicate with a
higher aspect of the client

01:11:02.130 --> 01:11:05.650 align:middle line:84%
himself or herself, which
Jung called the Self, which

01:11:05.650 --> 01:11:10.810 align:middle line:84%
in English would be capital
S. And this exchange

01:11:10.810 --> 01:11:13.830 align:middle line:84%
is happening through
symbolic means.

01:11:13.830 --> 01:11:16.460 align:middle line:84%
And the healing is
guided from within,

01:11:16.460 --> 01:11:21.280 align:middle line:84%
through the client's
own higher intelligence.

01:11:21.280 --> 01:11:26.600 align:middle line:84%
So it is what Jung called
the individuation process.

01:11:26.600 --> 01:11:29.740 align:middle line:84%
So when we work with nonordinary
states, with holotropic states,

01:11:29.740 --> 01:11:31.350 align:middle line:90%
we are not the therapists.

01:11:31.350 --> 01:11:32.930 align:middle line:90%
We are not the fixers.

01:11:32.930 --> 01:11:34.830 align:middle line:90%
We are sort of co-adventurers.

01:11:34.830 --> 01:11:38.990 align:middle line:84%
We are people who are creating
supportive environment

01:11:38.990 --> 01:11:43.560 align:middle line:84%
and we support the process,
even if we don't intellectually

01:11:43.560 --> 01:11:45.550 align:middle line:90%
understand it.

01:11:45.550 --> 01:11:47.930 align:middle line:84%
Now I see a very
different situation

01:11:47.930 --> 01:11:53.120 align:middle line:84%
than I remember from
the Freudian years,

01:11:53.120 --> 01:11:57.090 align:middle line:84%
where the very typical situation
is that after years of therapy,

01:11:57.090 --> 01:12:00.020 align:middle line:84%
you can give lectures about
what's wrong with you.

01:12:00.020 --> 01:12:02.560 align:middle line:90%
But the problem is still there.

01:12:02.560 --> 01:12:05.210 align:middle line:84%
Whereas in nonordinary
states, it's

01:12:05.210 --> 01:12:08.140 align:middle line:84%
much more common that
the problem disappears,

01:12:08.140 --> 01:12:10.290 align:middle line:84%
the symptom disappears,
but we don't quite

01:12:10.290 --> 01:12:15.130 align:middle line:84%
understand the past ways
to which it happened.

01:12:15.130 --> 01:12:17.110 align:middle line:90%
So I have run out of time.

01:12:17.110 --> 01:12:18.880 align:middle line:84%
So thank you very much
for your patience.

01:12:18.880 --> 01:12:21.930 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

01:12:21.930 --> 01:13:07.300 align:middle line:90%